comment: Ran out of pilsner malt, hence the 2-row. Yeast from a local brewery, BSI570, very phenolic and sweet fruity aroma, low floc. Nice big slurry, so should have a quick start...
Don't have any traditional Euro hops on hand, both are billed as "clean" bittering hops, with some citrus/floral aroma, so it should turn out decently.
